<div>
  <p>
    This demo uses the
    <code>sizes</code>
    attribute combined with
    <code>scrcset</code>. The
    <code>srcset</code>
    attribute in this demo uses width descriptors:
  </p>
  {{! prettier-ignore }}
  <code><pre>srcset=&quot;/image-640.jpg 640w, /image-1280.jpg 1280w, /image-1920.jpg 1920w&quot;</pre></code>
  <p>
    The width descriptor matches the image's intrinsic width. So the file
    <code>/image-640.jpg</code>
    has an intrinsic width of
    <code>640w</code>. This is combined with the
    <code>sizes</code>, where we inform the browser at what display size the
    image will be displayed on different viewports.
  </p>
  {{! prettier-ignore }}
  <code><pre>sizes=&quot;(min-width: 540px) 640px, calc(100vw - 2rem)&quot;</pre></code>
  <p>
    On devices with a viewport larger than 540px, the image will always be shown
    at 640px, while on smaller viewports it will occupy the viewport width minus
    2rem.
  </p>
  <div class="gallery">
